def save_fig(fig_id, tight_layout=True, fig_extension="png", resolution=300):
    path = os.path.join(IMAGES_PATH, fig_id + "." + fig_extension)
    print("Saving figure", fig_id)
    if tight_layout:
        plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(path, format=fig_extension, dpi=resolution)

#check data summary 
def summary_stat(df):
    pd.set_option('display.float_format',lambda x : '%.2f'% x)
    print("\n-------------Columns in the data--------------------------------")
    print (df.columns.tolist())
    print("\n-------------Variable Types-------------------------------")
    print  (df.info())
    print("\n---------------------------------------------")
    print("Number of columns are {} and Number of rows are {} respectively.".format(df.shape[1], df.shape[0]))
    print("Number of Nulls - {}.".format(df.isnull().sum().sum()))
    nans=df.iloc[df.index[df.isnull().all(1)]]
    print("All rows are Nulls -{}.".format(len(nans)))

def pct_miss(data):
    columns = data.columns
    tot=len(data)
    percent_missing= data.isnull().sum() * 100 / len(data)
    missing_count=data.isnull().sum()
    missdf = pd.DataFrame({'column_name': columns,'miss_count': missing_count,'pct_missing': percent_missing,'total counts':tot})
    missdf.sort_values('miss_count',ascending=False, inplace=True)
    return missdf.to_csv('missing_pct.csv')
    #return missdf

# level of categorical variables 
def char_level(chardf):
    columns = chardf.columns
    levels=chardf.nunique()
    char= pd.DataFrame({'column_name': columns,'levels': levels})
    char.sort_values('levels',ascending=False, inplace=True)
    return char

# check num variable distribution 
def num_distr(numdf):
# check the distribution of numvars  and save as pandas dataframe,  transpose the output
    pd.set_option('display.float_format',lambda x : '%.2f'% x)
    stats = numdf.describe().transpose()
    stats['miss_count']= numdf.shape[0] - stats['count'].astype(int)
    stats['missing_pct'] =( numdf.shape[0] - stats['count'].astype(int))/numdf.shape[0]
    stats['var']=stats.index
       # output to a csv file 
    stats.to_csv('num_dist.csv')
    return stats 

# target distribution 
def target_rate(df,y):
    tot_tag_rate = df[y].sum()*1.0/df.shape[0]
    return   tot_tag_rate

# EDA chart 
def univariate_numvar(df, gr,xvar,  yvar=None,dec=None):
    x = df[xvar]
    
    # print (' Variable :{}'.format(x))
    #print (' Number of missing :{}'.format(x.isna().sum()))
    
    f, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))
    

    # quatile bining 
    srs, binEdges = pd.qcut(x, gr, labels=False, retbins=True,duplicates='drop')
    ax1.bar(range(len(x.groupby(srs).count().index)), x.groupby(srs).count() )
   


    # legend
    if np.median(np.array(binEdges)) > 100:
        rangeformat = '%.f - %.f'
    else:
        rangeformat = '%.2f - %.2f'
    textstr = '\n'.join([('Bin%d: ' + rangeformat) % (i, binEdges[i], binEdges[i+1]) for i in range(len(binEdges)-1)])
    
    
    ax1.text(1.15, 0.98, textstr, transform=ax1.transAxes, fontsize=14, verticalalignment='top')
    
    # title
    ax1.set_xlabel(' %s' %(xvar))
    ax1.set_title('Plot of Variable: %s ' % (xvar), fontsize=16)
    ax1.set_ylabel('Counts')

  
    # If target is provided, plotted on the same chart
    if yvar:
        y = df[yvar]
        # second y axis
        ax2 = ax1.twinx()
        ax2.grid(False)
        plt.plot(y.groupby(srs).mean().index, y.groupby(srs).mean(), 'yo-' ,label=yvar)
        
        if dec:
            p=df[dec]
            plt.plot(p.groupby(srs).mean().index, p.groupby(srs).mean(), color='g',label=dec)
        plt.legend(loc='right')
      

    plt.show()
    #pp.savefig()
In [4]:
def catplot(df,x,y,  plot):
    print (' Variable :{}'.format(x))
    cnts=df[x].value_counts()

    cnt_pct=df[x].value_counts()/df[x].count() 
    avgtg=df.groupby([x])[y].mean()
    cy_df=pd.DataFrame({'Counts': cnts,'counts_pct':cnt_pct,'Avg_Target_Rate':avgtg })
    cy_df[x]=cy_df.index
    cy_df=cy_df.sort_index(axis=0, ascending=True)
   
    
    display(cy_df)
    
       
    if plot:


        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
        plt.clf()

        sns.barplot(x, 'Counts',data=cy_df, alpha=1,color='b')


        plt.title('Plot of Variable :{}'.format(x),fontsize=16)
        plt.ylabel('Counts', fontsize=16)
        plt.xlabel(x, fontsize=16)
        plt.xticks(rotation='vertical') 
        plt.grid(False)
        
        # line chart 
        ax2 = plt.twinx()  # instantiate a second axes that shares the same x-axis   
        ax2.grid(False)
        ax2.plot(cy_df[['Avg_Target_Rate']].values, linestyle='-', marker='o', linewidth=2.0,color='y')
        ax2.set_ylabel('Avg_Target_Rate')

       
        plt.show()
        #pp.savefig()
    return cy_df

In [18]:
def bi_var(x):
    if x=='yes':
        return 1
    elif x=='no':
        return 0
    else:
        return -99
 # for numberical variable , only age has missing   
def neg_var(x):
    if x >0 :
        return 'gt0'
    elif x==0 :
        return 'eq0'
    elif x<0:
        return 'ls0'
    else :
        return 'NULL'
    
def day_wk(x):
    if 0<=x<=7:
        return '1-7 day'
    elif 7<x<=15:
        return '7-15 day'
    elif 15<x<=31:
        return '15-31 day'
    else:
        return 'NULL'
def day_wk2(x):
    if 0<=x<=7:
        return '1-15 day'
    elif 7<x<=15:
        return '1-15 day'
    elif 15<x<=31:
        return '15-31 day'
    else:
        return 'NULL'

# derive some new variables to check
num_df['y']=np.where(df['y']=='yes', 1,0)
# duration in hours and minutes -no need 
num_df['duration_min']=num_df['duration']/60
num_df['duration_hr']=num_df['duration']/3600
# negative and zero balance , pick  to see 
num_df['balance_ind']=num_df['balance'].apply(neg_var)
# zero vs non-zero -remove 3 records
num_df['duration_ind']=num_df['duration'].apply(neg_var)
# -1 indicate not contact previously , pick this 
num_df['pdays_ind']=num_df['pdays'].apply(neg_var)
# # of time contacted previouly , no need 
num_df['previous_ind']=num_df['previous'].apply(neg_var)
# days to 7,15,30 days -pick this variable 
num_df['day_ind']=num_df['day'].apply(day_wk)
num_df['day_ind2']=num_df['day'].apply(day_wk2)

def job(x):
    if x in ['unemployed', 'self-employed','NULL','unknown'] : return '0-unemploymed/self/unknown'
    elif x in ['housemaid','services'] : return 'housemaid/service'
    elif x in ['retired','student']: return 'retired/student'
    elif x in  ['entrepreneur','management']: return 'management/enterpreneur'
    else : return x
def bi_var(x):
    if x=='yes':
        return 1
    else:
        return 0
def qrt(x):  
    if x in ['jan','feb','mar']:return 1 
    elif x in ['apr','may' ,'jun']:return 2 
    elif x in ['jul', 'aug','sep']: return 3
    else: return 4
char_df['marital_ind']=np.where(char_df['marital']=='married',1,0)    
char_df['education']=char_df['education'].replace('NULL', 'unknown')   
char_df['job_grp']=char_df['job'].apply(job) 
char_df['loan_ind']=char_df['loan'].apply(bi_var)
char_df['housing_ind']=char_df['housing'].apply(bi_var)
char_df['default_ind']=char_df['default'].apply(bi_var)
char_df['contact_cell_ind']=char_df['contact'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in ['cellular'] else 0)
char_df['poutcome_suc_ind']=char_df['poutcome'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in ['success'] else 0)
# not that useful , same target rate 
char_df['poutcome_fail_ind']=char_df['poutcome'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in ['failure'] else 0)
char_df['qtr'] = char_df['month'].map(qrt)

char_ind=['marital_ind','education','job_grp','loan_ind','housing_ind','default_ind','contact_cell_ind','poutcome_suc_ind','poutcome_fail_ind','qtr']
for char in char_ind :
   catplot(char_df,char,'y',  plot=True)
